ummary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test coverage needs**\\n\\nI’m considering the phrase \\\"before meaningful coverage is reachable.\\\" Maybe only certain tests require this rather than all of them. I see that generated tests might use ObjectMapper and annotations, but the existing suite have add-opens included. If it's missing, one coverage-significant test would fail. The user is clear: they want a decision without modifying the repository. It seems the current scaffold may already have what it needs, but it's good to think about risks just in case.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Jackson introspection issues**\\n\\nI should mention the JDK/platform version because there’s an enum introspection failure without opens. The behavior of `JacksonAnnotationIntrospector.findEnumValue` has changed in the newer shaded Jackson, leading to an existing assertion failure, not due to setup. I'm wondering about multi-release classes on JDK 25, possibly with Native Image. It’s important to assess risks, especially with shaded Jackson package resources and module-info. Tests should avoid adding unshaded Jackson because it bundles shaded Jackson. Ensuring valid JSON is also key for reachability metadata regarding test beans and resources.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"parquet-jackson is a self-contained shaded Jackson artifact with no runtime Maven services, Docker service, or external dependency requirement, but meaningful tests that exercise Jackson enum-type introspection need java.util opened on modern JDKs.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use the shaded Parquet Jackson APIs, e.g. shaded.parquet.com.fasterxml.jackson.*. Do not add normal com.fasterxml.jackson dependencies. If tests exercise shaded Jackson internals such as ClassUtil.findEnumType on EnumSet or EnumMap, configure JVM test execution and native-image build/run arguments with --add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED; otherwise those paths fail with InaccessibleObjectException on JDK 17+.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The current failure shown for JacksonAnnotationIntrospector.findEnumValue appears to be a version behavior/API expectation change in the shaded Jackson code, not missing deterministic setup.\",\n    \"Avoid tests that depend on unshaded Jackson packages; parquet-jackson relocates Jackson under shaded.parquet.com.fasterxml.jackson.\",\n    \"Coverage involving internal shaded Jackson reflection may be JDK-sensitive unless the java.util module open is preserved.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a287bdef3de3971016a3fc4996b488197a00a63905c8323c5\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 881, "output": 783, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24192, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782563983466, "responseId": "resp_0a287bdef3de3971016a3fc48ff2888197a1207f537e22816e"}, "toolResults": []}
